﻿# nlp-cluster-extract

Portfolio-grade NLP toolkit for document clustering and information extraction.

## Quickstart (Windows)

```powershell
py -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\activate
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
pip install -e .
python scripts\generate_sample_data.py
nlpce --help
```

## What’s included

- TF-IDF + KMeans clustering
- Keyword extraction + entity/PII extraction (planned)
- Typer-based CLI
- Synthetic sample data generator

## CLI

- `nlpce sample-data` generates `data/sample_docs.csv` if missing
- `nlpce cluster` runs clustering and writes outputs
- `nlpce extract` runs keyword + pattern extraction

## Project layout

```

## Clustering demo

```powershell
nlpce cluster --input data/sample_docs.csv --text-col text --k 6 --out outputs/run1
```

Outputs written to `outputs/run1`:

- `clustered_docs.csv` with `doc_id`, `title`, `cluster_id`, and `snippet`
- `clusters.json` with metrics, cluster sizes, top terms, and representative doc ids
- `report.md` human-readable summary

## Extraction demo

```powershell
nlpce extract --input data/sample_docs.csv --text-col text --out outputs/extract1 --top-k 12
```

Outputs written to `outputs/extract1`:

- `extraction.json` with per-doc keywords and extracted patterns
- `keywords_summary.md` with global keyword counts (and per-cluster highlights if `clustered_docs.csv` exists)

## Optional Streamlit demo

```powershell
pip install streamlit
streamlit run app/streamlit_app.py
